                type="document" xml:id="d45">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On May 18 the Intergovernmental Study Group on Germany (<gloss target="#t_ISG1"
                        >ISG</gloss>) held its final plenary meeting and agreed on the texts of the
                    various reports on restitution, reparations, contractual relations, and debt
                    settlements. In a brief concluding report, IGG/P(51)116 Final, dated May 16, not
                    printed (<gloss target="#t_CFM1">CFM</gloss> files, lot M–88, box 197), the
                    study group stated that it had considered the subjects listed in the Foreign
                    Ministers directive of September 1950 and the Brussels directive of December
                    1950 and had prepared nine reports for the Governments on these topics, thus
                    completing the discussion of all aspects of its agenda.</p>
                <p>Following the plenary the <gloss target="#t_ISG1">ISG</gloss> representatives met
                    with the Benelux delegates, briefed them on the reports, and informed them of
                    the conclusion of the study group’s work.</p>
            </div>
